savitha moorthy the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events no events found you are here home people savitha moorthy savitha moorthy graduate dissertation fellow 2004 05 education savitha moorthy is writing a dissertation that explores the gendered nature of the english learning experiences of adult immigrants to the united states her project takes seriously the idea that literacy is a women's issue and examines how for poor immigrant women in the united states english language literacy is an issue of social justice moorthy a ph d candidate in the school of education highlights the unique problems that women face in connecting the english they learn inside the classroom with their lives outside it by embedding itself in the concrete struggles of poor women this dissertation reclaims pragmatic concerns like literacy and education back into the feminist agenda and argues for programmatic models that take gender differences into account donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
